<subSubSection id="F32E1B58D914CFCB3100A6D9BC040E3A" pageId="6" pageNumber="171" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="698E3CF89DD037236633DB06404F0B9E" pageId="6" pageNumber="171">Distribution and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA1A261B5C8EF464ECC2859D25455D11" pageId="6" pageNumber="171">This species is known only from southern Arizona, although its distribution likely extends into Mexico. The larva and its food plants are unknown. Adults were collected in July, August, and September.</paragraph>
